#!/usr/bin/env ssc
---
name: health-defaults
description: Minimal serve() — exercises built-in /_health and /_ready
---

# Health defaults

A `serve(port)` call with no user routes should still expose
`GET /_health` and `GET /_ready` returning `200 {"status":"ok"}`.

```scalascript
println("Listening on http://localhost:8769/  (built-in /_health and /_ready)")
serve(8769)
```
